By Juliet Ebirim Yawnaija Production is set to present a thrilling and exciting satire, PO!! by award-winning OAP, actor and producer, Steve Onu popularly known as YAW and comedian cum OAP, Uba Michael popularly known as Ogbolo.  The show which will hold from June 10th to June 12th, 2022 at Terra Kulture, Victoria Island, Lagos, will feature top Nigerian comedians and some cast members of TV comedy show, ‘MY FLATMATES’ ; Titus, Prosper,  Mimi, Obus and Chief Donatus among others. Directed by Kenneth Uphopho and written by Nollywood actor, Femi Branch, the show will also feature famous old and new school music artists in Nigeria.  Yaw held his first stage play in 2009 alongside talented comedian, Koffi. Since then he has shared the stage with the likes of Owen Gee, Funke Akindele, Mc Abbey, Julius Agwu to mention a few.  Speaking about the upcoming event, Yaw says: “I haven’t done my stage play in 5years. This year I decided to and as you know, mine is not just about comedy, it is about advocacy and educating the minds of everyone. I also decided to do this at this time because much hasn’t changed in terms of governance.”  Yaw has been known to bring exceptional talents on stage to deliver unusual play, dance and musical performances.